{
  "texts": [
    "The agent's task is to navigate the environment and reach the target location based on the natural language instructions.",
    "This process requires the agent to parse and comprehend each step of the instructions, match them with the visual perception of the environment, plan a path, and take actions to complete the navigation task as instructed.",
    "VLMs and LLMs play a crucial role in VLN tasks as they can comprehend vision and language cues to significantly enhance the agent's navigation performance in complex environments.",
    "Based on different navigation scenarios, we categorise these works into indoor navigation, outdoor navigation, and web navigation.",
    "The general approach of VLM-based VLN is shown in Fig. 6."
  ]
}